OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Wed 8 Jul to Fri 17 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure will dominate across
OL,7,FEngland and Wales into next week,
OL,8,Flikely extending its influence into
OL,9,Fthe northern UK with time. This will
OL,10,Fbring dry and warm conditions with
OL,11,Fplenty of sunshine for much of England
OL,12,Fand Wales, but there is a chance of
OL,13,Fthunderstorms at times. Scotland and
OL,14,FNorthern Ireland will see more cloud
OL,15,Fat first, with periods of rain at
OL,16,Ftimes. Through next week the high
OL,17,Fpressure may extend northwards to
OL,18,Fbring periods of drier and warmer
OL,19,Fweather to most of Scotland and
OL,20,FNorthern Ireland. Winds will be light
OL,21,Fto moderate for most, though stronger
OL,22,Faround northern hills and coasts near
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Flow pressure systems. Temperatures
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fbecoming widely warm, perhaps locally
OL,25,Fhot in parts of the southeast,
OL,26,Falthough not as hot nor humid as seen
